        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2661097819" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13010761034614467477">Another fabulous Poirot novel and an easy 4 stars<br/><br/>More tomorrow, hopefully 😬<br/><br/>Well for various reasons it has been considerably more than just a single day later, why ? well all sorts really, family visits, car MOTs, helping neighbours etc etc.<br/><br/>Anyway, I have this vague memory of seeing the great David Suchet&apos;s version of this story, and I therefore knew there <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[ was a twist at the end, I just couldn&apos;t remember how it finally panned out  <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.<br/>So all in all this was a great no</span>
  <span id="freeText13010761034614467477" style="display:none">Another fabulous Poirot novel and an easy 4 stars<br /><br />More tomorrow, hopefully 😬<br /><br />Well for various reasons it has been considerably more than just a single day later, why ? well all sorts really, family visits, car MOTs, helping neighbours etc etc.<br /><br />Anyway, I have this vague memory of seeing the great David Suchet's version of this story, and I therefore knew there <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ was a twist at the end, I just couldn't remember how it finally panned out  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.<br />So all in all this was a great novel in which Poirot appears about a third of the way through. After that though his presence is virtually full time as he applies the "lgc"s to the problem in front of him. Can he prove the accused (and charged) innocent or will he find as most people believe that she was guilty as charged.<br />Poirot is on top form as he cajoles, interrogates and schmoozes all the players in this drama to come to his conclusion, that is played out in the courtroom.<br /><br />So why wasn't this 5 stars, erm well in all honesty I cannot put my finger on it, it just wasn't. Was it Poirot appearing late, no I don't think so, as I was enjoying the book despite Poirot; was it the twist, well again no because it is well written; I just think it wasn't quite as good as some Poirot novels. Ooh one thing that I thought was less than wonderful was <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ Roddy Wellman. I just never really warmed to him <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13010761034614467477" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

