<span id="freeTextContainer17869971306187503368">One of my favorites (along with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16424.Peril_at_End_House__Hercule_Poirot___8_' title='Peril at End House (Hercule Poirot, #8) by Agatha Christie' rel='nofollow noopener'>Peril at End House</a>, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/131359.Death_on_the_Nile__Hercule_Poirot___17_' title='Death on the Nile (Hercule Poirot, #17) by Agatha Christie' rel='nofollow noopener'>Death on the Nile</a>, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16342.Cat_Among_the_Pigeons__Hercule_Poirot___34_' title='Cat Among the Pigeons (Hercule Poirot, #34) by Agatha Christie' rel='nofollow noopener'>Cat Among the Pigeons</a>, and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16328.The_Murder_of_Roger_Ackroyd__Hercule_Poirot___4_' title='The Murder of Roger Ackroyd (Hercule Poirot, #4) by Agatha Christie' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Murder of Roger Ackroyd</a>) that I continue to reread.<br/><br/>Elinor Carlisle is an elegant, intelligent heiress. Although on the surface she is always calm and unruffled, she is desperately in love with Rodney Welham, a childhood friend who is even more fastidious than Elinor--and who has no idea how intensely Elinor feels about him.<br/><br/>They are expecting a large inheritance from their aunt who is very ill. W</span>
  <span id="freeText17869971306187503368" style="display:none">One of my favorites (along with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16424.Peril_at_End_House__Hercule_Poirot___8_" title="Peril at End House (Hercule Poirot, #8) by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">Peril at End House</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/131359.Death_on_the_Nile__Hercule_Poirot___17_" title="Death on the Nile (Hercule Poirot, #17) by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">Death on the Nile</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16342.Cat_Among_the_Pigeons__Hercule_Poirot___34_" title="Cat Among the Pigeons (Hercule Poirot, #34) by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">Cat Among the Pigeons</a>, and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16328.The_Murder_of_Roger_Ackroyd__Hercule_Poirot___4_" title="The Murder of Roger Ackroyd (Hercule Poirot, #4) by Agatha Christie" rel="nofollow noopener">The Murder of Roger Ackroyd</a>) that I continue to reread.<br /><br />Elinor Carlisle is an elegant, intelligent heiress. Although on the surface she is always calm and unruffled, she is desperately in love with Rodney Welham, a childhood friend who is even more fastidious than Elinor--and who has no idea how intensely Elinor feels about him.<br /><br />They are expecting a large inheritance from their aunt who is very ill. When an anonymous letter arrives warning of an "interloper", the two go visit their aunt. While there, they meet the beautiful Mary Gerard, a young girl home from an education their aunt has paid for.<br /><br />The greatest pleasure for me in this text are the characters and their relationships. The plot is interesting but it is the people I find most interesting. There is of course murder and my favorite detective, Hercule Poirot, on hand to ensure that justice is served.<br /><br />A great escape read.</span>
